In mathematics, a '''Lie-* algebra''' is a [[D-module]] with a Lie* bracket. They were introduced by [[Alexander Beilinson]] and [[Vladimir Drinfeld]] ({{harvtxt|Beilinson|Drinfeld|2004|loc=section 2.5.3}}), and are similar to the '''conformal algebras''' discussed by {{harvtxt|Kac|1998}} and to '''vertex Lie algebras'''.

